.TH "mdio_set_flag" 9 "mdio_set_flag" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mdio_set_flag \- set or clear flag in an MDIO register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mdio_set_flag
.BI "(const struct mdio_if_info *mdio "  ","
.BI "int prtad "  ","
.BI "int devad "  ","
.BI "u16 addr "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ","
.BI "bool sense "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mdio" 12
MDIO interface
.IP "prtad" 12
PHY address
.IP "devad" 12
MMD address
.IP "addr" 12
Register address
.IP "mask" 12
Mask for flag (single bit set)
.IP "sense" 12
New value of flag
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This debounces changes: it does not write the register if the flag
already has the proper value.  Returns 0 on success, negative on error.
